I was getting the following error when calling Keyring from Apache on Windows
 KeyError: 'USERPROFILE'\r

I was able to hack it to work by updating util/platform.py.  See the updated function below.  This is not a general fix, but it allowed me to get past this problem and I wanted to share my solution.

```
#!python
def _data_root_Windows():
    try:
        root = os.environ['LOCALAPPDATA']
    except KeyError:
        **if os.environ.has_key('USERPROFILE'):
            root = os.path.join(os.environ['USERPROFILE'], 'Local Settings')
        else:
            root = os.path.join("C:\Program Files (x86)\Apache Software Foundation\Apache2.2\conf", 'Local Settings')**
    return os.path.join(root, 'Python Keyring')

```

