exabgp 3.4.12 on FreeBSD will sometimes pass JSON state messages via the API, other times it will not.  On one run,a process will receive state messages of type state with neighbor state of up, down, connected.  After a stop and restart of the exabgp process, perhaps of these state messages will be received.  Restart again, maybe they will show up -- varies from run to run, seems completely non-deterministic.  This makes it difficult for a process to remove installed routes when not receiving down notifications about a neighbor.

Messages of interests:

{
    "counter": 1,
    "exabgp": "3.4.8",
    "host": "some.host",
    "neighbor": {
        "address": {
            "local": "fec0::1:1",
            "peer": "fec0::1:2"
        },
        "asn": {
            "local": "65003",
            "peer": "65004"
        },
        "ip": fec0::1:2",
        "state": "connected"
    },
    "pid": "36591",
    "ppid": "1",
    "time": 1440603404.16,
    "type": "state"
}

And also those where neighbor "state": "up" and "state": "down".

